author: Inside Edition
description: "Saturday Night Live" is back, and the show wasted no time poking fun at President Donald Trump. The host was #BadBunny, whose selection last week as the #SuperBowl halftime performer drew intense backlash from Trump supporters. Bad Bunny hit back at that criticism.
title: SNL Wastes No Time Poking Fun At Donald Trump #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Pandora Kjolsrud, 17, and 18-year-old Clark Evans were found shot to death near a remote hiking trail in Arizona after a Memorial Day outing. Inside Edition spoke with Evans’ heartbroken mother. Detectives say accused killer Thomas Brown was camping near Arizona's Mount Ord. He told police he flew his drone around the mountain. After the bodies of the teens were found, investigators say Brown called a police help line. Detectives say his DNA was found at the crime scene.
title: Suspect Arrested In Murder Of 2 Teens On Arizona Camping Trip

author: Inside Edition
description: Prominent rock climber 23-year-old Balin Miller fell to his death while going down El Capitan in Yosemite National Park during a livestream. Inside Edition spoke to his grieving mother, Jeanine, and brother, Dillon. "My soul is shattered, shattered. Nothing is going to fill it ever," Jeanine says. El Capitan is one of the world's most challenging climbs. The vertical rock formation is made of pure granite and rises 3,000 feet from base to summit.
title: Mother Of Rock Climber Balin Miller Speaks Out After His Tragic Death

author: Inside Edition
description: "Saturday Night Live" is back and wasted no time poking fun at President Donald Trump. The host was Bad Bunny, whose selection last week as the Super Bowl halftime performer drew intense backlash from Trump supporters. Bad Bunny has been a critic of ICE and the Trump administration, and he hit back at the criticism. Meanwhile, First Lady Melania Trump was at the Navy celebrations Sunday.
title: 'SNL' Wastes No Time Poking Fun At President Donald Trump

author: Inside Edition
description: This teen cross country runner passes out over and over again after finishing her races. Inside Edition spoke to 17-year-old Jewel Gannon. The problem is so severe, she started asking people to try to catch her at the finish line. Just last year, the teen from South Dakota passed out 18 times. Gannon was recently diagnosed with POTS, a condition that causes heart palpitations and dizziness. Inside Edition spoke with Maimonides Health neurologist Dr. Leah Kroll.
title: Why Does This Teen Cross Country Runner Keep Fainting After A Race?

author: Inside Edition
description: The mansion of a prominent South Carolina judge went up in flames, leaving many questioning if it was arson. Circuit Court Judge Diane Goodstein was on a walk when the fire started. Her husband and son were injured while escaping the flames. The fire was reportedly triggered by an "explosion." Investigators are at the scene combing through wreckage for signs of arson. Goldstein had reportedly been getting death threats after she ruled against President Donald Trump over voter privacy laws.
title: Investigators Look For Possible Sign Of Arson After Judge's House Fire

author: Inside Edition
description: Henny is a 3-year-old yellow belly/ball Python mix who got out of her cage and was missing for weeks. She finally turned up at an In-N-Out Burger joint 50 miles from her home in San Bernardino, California. The family says she probably hitched a ride on a passing car, since she is known to wrap herself around their vehicle. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Escaped Pet Python Found Weeks Later At In-N-Out Burger 50 Miles From Home

author: Inside Edition
description: Ignoring a school bus's flashing lights and stop signs could land a driver a $1000 fine in Atlanta, but how do you ticket a driverless car?
title: Can Cops Ticket Driverless Cars? #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: An American basketball player possibly faces the death penalty or a lengthy prison sentence after being arrested in Indonesia on drug charges. Jarred Shaw, 35, used to play in the Indonesian Basketball League for the Tangerhawks. That was until May, when reports say he received a package in the mail from Thailand containing 132 cannabis gummies, which are not legal in Indonesia, and where some offenders have been sentenced to death by firing squad. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: American Athlete Arrested On Cannabis Charges Faces Death Penalty In Indonesia

author: Inside Edition
description: In May 2005, then-8-year-old Shasta Groene and her brother were kidnapped by convicted serial killer and child molester Joseph Edward Duncan after he murdered their family.
title: How Shasta Groene Survived Kidnapper Who Killed Her Family #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Misty Combs from Kentucky stepped in to help a drunk raccoon in distress.
title: Kentucky Nurse Gives CPR To Moonshine-Drunk Raccoon  #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Months after two teens were found shot to death in a park, investigators have made an arrest. The Maricopa County Sheriff says Thomas Brown, 31, has been taken into custody in connection with the deaths of 18-year-old Pandora Kjolsrud and 17-year-old Evan Clark. Their bodies were found on Mount Ord in Arizona on May 27th. Investigators say tips from people camping in the area that day helped lead them to this suspect. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 31-Year-Old Man Accused Of Killing 2 Teens Camping In Arizona

author: Inside Edition
description: One man learned he was accused of decapitating a sea lion when he saw his image on a wanted poster offering a $20,000 reward to anyone who could identify him.
title: California Man Cleared In Sea Lion Death #shorts
